  "body": "I find \"Get started\" to be a pretty ambiguous call to action - I was hoping for some additional context before jumping straight into the flow to become a validator. I suggest we add a secondary callout, e.g. \"view requirements\" that navigates visitors to the [checklist page](https://launchpad.ethereum.org/checklist), which gives a solid overview of hardware & technical skills required.\r\n\r\nI think this could help people to quickly come to a decision on if staking is something they still want to do & if they're prepared to move forward with.\r\n\r\ne.g. something like\r\n![Image 2021-02-03 at 4 08 46 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8097623/106825740-58453900-663a-11eb-9f17-35be95a883a4.jpg)\r\n",
